commentTextItems.html: bowled him! Neck and crop! What a brilliant delivery; just back of a length, the perfect wicket-to-wicket delivery to clip the top of off. Great finish, well done Sri Lanka, well done Fernando. Great stuff!

commentPostTextItems.html: Well, this has been excellent stuff from Sri Lanka, holding their nerve, bowling well and that's a great match and they deserve the win. Good batting from Nixon and Bopara, sneaking up on the outside and taking England close, but with no cigar. There will be some consolation, though, as the defeat is so narrow, it won't have much of a detrimental effect on their net run rate if it comes down to it.

This is the kind of match the tournament's been crying out for and, after Sri Lanka are involved in another close finish, here's Fernando: "A fantastic game, I think I did well today. I think the boys are playing really well." He explains that Jayawardene told him to bowl in the block hole, no slower balls, and his advice paid off.

Thanks for joining us today, hope you've enjoyed it as much as we have, and that's halfway through the Super Eight stage now. The next World Cup match is this Saturday, when Bangladesh take on South Africa, so do join us then.

commentPostTextItems.html: Brilliant bowling from Malinga, keeping his head here. It's great that Nixon and Bopara took England so close and made it a contest, but Sri Lanka have the upper hand now, and will deserve the win. A change of balls, by the way, seven balls to go now.

commentTextItems.html: outside off and that's another calm delivery from Malinga, very good indeed, that on the spot and just worked forward

commentPostTextItems.html: Jayawardene just coming over to have a word, Malinga smiling

commentTextItems.html: great delivery, Bopara moving outside leg to give himself room to plant that through the off side - that goes down the corridor and he was nowhere near it
takes that from outside off to drive it in front of midwicket
outside off, Bopara lays bat on that one, driving it to cover

commentPostTextItems.html: This is great to watch, whoever wins, it's so nice to have a contest

commentTextItems.html: another reverse sweep and that goes fine - the fielder chases it down, just gets a hand on it, but merely helps it on its way

commentPostTextItems.html: Malinga is warming up now - 19 from 12 balls. Where's your money now?
